<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>Written evidence Community Transport Association (TIC )</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.2pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Written evidence </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Community Transport Association</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> (TIC )</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 15.01pt; padding-left:20.99pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Introduction</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.2pt; text-indent:-32.2pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">1.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">This evidence is submitted by the Community Transport Association (CTA)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> a national charity providing leadership, learning and enterprise support to organisations delivering innovative and flexible transport solutions to achieve social change in their communities.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">  The CTA currently has around 1,500 member organisations.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.2pt; text-indent:-32.2pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">1.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The demand for community transport (CT) has increased </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">in recent years for a variety of reasons, particularly in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">isolated </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">areas. Services include</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">demand responsive</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> routes, dial-a-ride</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, voluntary car schemes, minibus hire, schedul</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ed bus services, wheels to w</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ork and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">patient/visitor tran</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">sport, as well as brokerage, training and community development.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.2pt; text-indent:-32.2pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">1.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">CTA welcomes the inclusion of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">CT in the Transport Committees inquiry and the opportunity to provide written</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">evidence.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> We would also welcome the opportunity to</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> provide further insights and ideas about the important role CT can plays in supporting isolated communities when oral evidence is being heard in the autumn.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 15.01pt; padding-left:20.99pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">The inquiry questions</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.2pt; text-indent:-32.2pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">2.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">How do Government and local authorities identify demand for passenger tran</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">sport in isolated communities (including rural and urban areas and island communities)?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.2pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 49.65pt; text-indent:-49.65pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">2.1.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">The Community Transport Association</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">:  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The CTA </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">provides a</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> voice for CT across the UK </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">with</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> a</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">long history of consulting members and the sector </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">and</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> articulat</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ing</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> the views</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> and needs of community based transport to policy makers at a national (and devolved) government level.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">  In so doing, it is able to comment on demand at a strategic level as it consults with operators around the country at regional events</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, members meetings</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> and via national conferences and through electronic communication groups.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 49.65pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 49.65pt; text-indent:-49.65pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">2.1.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Sub-r</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">egional/county CT consortia</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">:</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">We are seeing the development of</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> more</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">county/</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">sub-</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">regional bodies </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">supporting </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the development of community transport in their area</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, including</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">formally constituted consortia </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">of which</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Suffolk, Devon, Norfolk, Greater Manchester are all </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">good examples</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.  They can act as a conduit for communication with local government on the needs of CT providers and users.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 49.65pt; text-indent:-49.65pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">2.1.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Local authority consultation, research an</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">d transport departments:</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Local authorities </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">in some areas have an excellent record of consulting with both CT providers and CT users.  They commission their own research from time to time and transport department staff are frequently very knowledgeable on </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">policy and operational matters.  This experience is not universal, however, and the CT sector does struggle to engage with local authorities in many areas.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 49.65pt; text-indent:-49.65pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">2.1.4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">CT</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">A S</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">tate of the Sector (SOTS)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> reports</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">:</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The CTA researches and publishes its </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">S</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">OTS</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> reports in England (and other countries of the UK) in order to continually improve the available evidence base on CT.  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">These reports are </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">used to</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> build a better picture of CT service development across England.  This developmen</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">t reflects demand for service</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">s given the fact that CT services are established in direct response to identified user need.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 49.65pt; text-indent:-49.65pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">2.1.5</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Additional data sources</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">:</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Additional </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">publicly available research and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">data </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">analyses</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> will be used</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> by authorities to,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> such as:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="square" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 68.09pt; padding-left:7.51pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">DfT National Transport Survey </span><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/department-for-transport/series/national-travel-survey-statistics"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/department-for-transport/series/national-travel-survey-statistics</span></a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span></li><li style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 68.09pt; padding-left:7.51pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Census data</span></li><li style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 68.09pt; padding-left:7.51pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Annual</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> report</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ing to regulatory bodies</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> (</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Char</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ity Commission, Companies House etc</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">)</span></li><li style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 68.09pt; padding-left:7.51pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Transport surveys undertaken by  independent consultants</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> (eg </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">TAS Bus Monitor</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><a href="http://www.tas-passtrans.co.uk/content/index.php"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.tas-passtrans.co.uk/content/index.php</span></a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">)</span></li><li style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 68.09pt; padding-left:7.51pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Reports and data from </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Passenger Focus</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> (</span><a href="http://www.passengerfocus.org.uk/"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.passengerfocus.org.uk/</span></a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">) </span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.2pt; text-indent:-32.2pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">2.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">To what extent are the needs of different groups of passengers (e.g. people with disabilities, older people, young people) take</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">n into account in determining the provision of public transport to isolated communities?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.2pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 49.65pt; text-indent:-49.65pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">2.2.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Account taken of different groups’ requirement</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> is patchy</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">:</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">It is the experience of the CTA and the CT sector that the account taken of different groups’ needs can va</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ry widely by area.  Typically this can depend on the structure of the local authority transport department or even on the commitment of a small team or one individual.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 49.65pt; text-indent:-49.65pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">2.2.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">L</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">ack of network planning </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">du</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">e to the unregulated </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">bus </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">market</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">:</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">There is a lack of ability</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> to develop planned public transport networks outside London due to the de-regulated nature of the market.  This, in turn, means that it can be difficult for local authorities to influence the extent to which services take account of different passenger gr</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">oups in isolated areas.  The current economic climate also means that authorities are less able to support socially necessary bus services</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> through tendered routes.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 49.65pt; text-indent:-49.65pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">2.2.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Disadvantaged groups</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">’</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> needs are often an afterthought</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">:</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">It is understandable that transport authorities and operators seek to maximise the efficiency of the services they procure and/or operate.  Too often, however, the needs of marginalised groups of people are not fully considered</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> from the outset</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.  One clear </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">example of this is the failure to require the mandatory reimbursement </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">for transportation </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">of eligible concessionary pass holders on services </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">(such as community transport) </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">where no registered local bus service operates or where such services are inaccessible</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">to users.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">  The transport of young people is </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">also a particular </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">issue as no consistent concessionary arrangement exists for them across </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">England.  A national </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">young persons’ </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">concession would not only help to address the problems of isolation for young people,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> it would also help to build the habit at an early age of using public/community transport rather than assuming obtaining a car is the solution to all transport problems.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 49.65pt; text-indent:-49.65pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">2.2.4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Expectation that CT will pick up needs that others cannot meet:</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">In recent years we </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">have seen </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">a</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">growing assumption that CT </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">services will grow to fill the gaps </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">that commercial/statutory providers are unable to.  However, this increasing demand for CT services is set against a backdrop of decreasing funding which is stretching </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">many to break</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ing point.  Many CT</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> operators have sought to develop a social enterprise business model in order to become more sustainable.  This has been successful for some but has </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">also resulted in some struggling to manage new business relationships, particularly when</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> service commissioners do not appear prepared to pay for the full cost of the service received</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">There is </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">only </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">limited use of community audit or transport needs </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">analysis </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">at </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">d</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">istrict or </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">parish level, which could </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">potentially </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">better inform authorities of user</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> needs.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.2pt; text-indent:-32.2pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">2.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">What are the main challenges associated with providing better and more consistent bus and rail services to isolated communities? How can these challenges be overcome? </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 49.65pt; text-indent:-49.65pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">2.3.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Lack of integrated network planning</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">:</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The inability to plan and develop an integrated network is a challenge for </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">transport </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">authorities. The l</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ack of bus</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> route/market</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> regulation</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> which would allow this means that only profitable routes are developed in many areas.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">  This leads to an expectation th</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">at transport authorities and/or the CT sector will pick up on the needs of those who cannot access commercial bu</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> services.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 49.65pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 49.65pt; text-indent:-49.65pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">2.3.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Silo funding mentality</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">:</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">L</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ocal authorities, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">health </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">agencies, government departments and other bodies </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">appear to be</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">trying to protect</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">their </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">own budgets rather than </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">focusing on the strategic benefits of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">integrate</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">d</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> services.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The complex nature of the NHS and its particular transport requirements is a significant challenge in this respect.  There is evidence of the NHS </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">reducing </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">transport p</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">rovision </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">in some areas </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">by changing (tightening) eligibility criteria in order to reduce transport spend.  This merely has the effect of requiring someone else (typically CT or local authorities) to deliver the transport.  It is not unusual for the CT secto</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">r to deliver transport to health because the NHS will not or cannot pay for it.  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">In many cases </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the charitable/voluntary sector is </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">not receiving full cost recovery for services provided and so </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">it </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">is, in effect, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">subsidising </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">statutory</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> sector (eg the NHS)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 49.65pt; text-indent:-49.65pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">2.3.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Restrictive national policy:</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">In some cases, national policy is restricted to too narrow a field.  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">For instance, the lack of a </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">mandatory </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">obligation </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">reimburse local CT operators running Section 19 services at separate fares for transporting eligible </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">concessionary passengers means that many CT operators end up subsidising these passengers themselves.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 49.65pt; text-indent:-49.65pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">2.3.4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Service information:</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Information </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">on </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">existing services should be more visible and accessible</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> and more detailed guidance is required on </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">how isolated commu</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">nities </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">can </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">improve </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">public and community transport (for instance </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">by running </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">more services </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">themselves</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">).</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.2pt; text-indent:-32.2pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">2.4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">How effectively do Community Transport services address the needs of passengers in isolated communities? How could Community Transport be improved? </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 49.65pt; text-indent:-49.65pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">2.4.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">C</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">om</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">munity transport</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> is </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">based on user need</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">:</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">CT is flexible and r</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">esponsive to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">local </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">need</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">as a sector.  It</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">understands passenger requirements</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> so services are devised to meet </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">their </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">need</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.  CT is the only sector of the public transport market that was co</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">nceived and designed to deliver</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> community development and equality of opportunity – it merely uses transport as the tool to do this.  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">There </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">has been </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">h</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">uge increase in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">demand </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">for CT </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">in recent years </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">but </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">at the same time, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">available funding has reduced </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the sector’s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> ability to service need is </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">becoming ever more </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">compromised</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 49.65pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 49.65pt; text-indent:-49.65pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">2.4.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">CTA State of the Sector reporting </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">illustrate</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">the impact of the sector:</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">  Three reports have now been published by the CTA (2009, 2010 and 2012) on the state of the CT sector in Englan</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">d.  The next report is due for publication in 2014.  Although covering the whole of England, the 2012 report also included a particular focus on rural areas, which is where many communities and individuals suffer from isolation.  Some of the key findings o</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">n the CT sector in England summarised in this report were:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="square" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 68.09pt; padding-left:7.51pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">There are at least 2,000 community transport organisations operating across England: nearly one-third of them are based in rural areas.</span></li><li style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 68.09pt; padding-left:7.51pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The sector provides 15 million plus passenger journeys each </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">year, of which 8 million are undertaken in rural areas.</span></li><li style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 68.09pt; padding-left:7.51pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">At least 42,000 voluntary groups use community transport every year.</span></li><li style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 68.09pt; padding-left:7.51pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">There are more than 60,000 people who volunteer with community transport organisations, of which 48,000 are in rural areas.</span></li><li style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 68.09pt; padding-left:7.51pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">At </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">least 10,600 people work in paid employment the community transport sector, of which over 2,000 are in rural areas.</span></li><li style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 68.09pt; padding-left:7.51pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The most common services provided by community transport organisations are group transport, community car schemes and door-to-door transport</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, but community transport organisations also provide a wide range of other services including community bus services, wheels to work schemes and driver training.</span></li><li style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 68.09pt; padding-left:7.51pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Community bus route registrations are rising very fast following the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">changes introduced in the</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Local </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">T</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ransport Act 2008.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 49.65pt; text-indent:-49.65pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">2.4.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Improving community transport:</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> The effectiveness of CT could still be greatly improved by implementing a number of measures.  These include:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Investing in growth through transport</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="square" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 68.09pt; padding-left:7.51pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Mandatory </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">reimbursement of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">concessionary travel</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> should be extended to include Section 19 CT services operated at sepa</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">rate fares.</span></li><li style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 68.09pt; padding-left:7.51pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Grant and other funding for CT shou</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ld be protected and expanded.  However, c</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">entral and local Government need to understand that is and investment in growth and sustainability</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> for isolated local communities and not a short term subsidy for service operators.</span></li><li style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 68.09pt; padding-left:7.51pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Central/local government should require all publicly funded transport to be shared/brokered/integrated</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span></li><li style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 68.09pt; padding-left:7.51pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The health sector (NHS) should be required </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">consult with the wider</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> public and community transport sector in order to ‘transport proof’ its strategy and policy before implementation.</span></li><li style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 68.09pt; padding-left:7.51pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">BSOG applied to CT should be ring-fenced and consideration should be given to making ‘red diesel’ available for community based non-profit s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ervices.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Permits &amp; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">operator </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">licensing</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="square" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 68.09pt; padding-left:7.51pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Section 19 permit administration should be simplified.  A single designated body (the CTA) for the issue of permits could support and deliver such a system.  The CTA has an excellent long term track record in this ar</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ea.</span></li><li style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 68.09pt; padding-left:7.51pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Given the success of the CTA as a Section 19 Permit issuing body, VOSA’s role could be simplified by transferring Section 22 permit issuing to the CTA as well.</span></li><li style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 68.09pt; padding-left:7.51pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Bus market regulation </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">should be considered.  I</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ncreased network planning reduces carbon </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">emissions, makes operators more efficient</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> and supports employment and economic growth.</span></li><li style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 68.09pt; padding-left:7.51pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">CT operators should be able to deliver single occupancy contracts in small (fewer than 9 passenger seats) vehicles under Section 19 permits.</span></li><li style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 68.09pt; padding-left:7.51pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The requirement to charge se</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">parate fares when running Section 19 services in vehicles with fewer than 9 seats should be removed.</span></li><li style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 68.09pt; padding-left:7.51pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">In </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">isolated communities</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, CT operators should be allowed to run Section 22 community bus routes in vehi</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">cles with fewer than 9 passenge</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">r seats.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 75.6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Drivers </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">licensing</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 75.6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="square" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 68.09pt; padding-left:7.51pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Dri</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">vers who</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> first sat their standard (category B) car driving test </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">on or </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">after the</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> 1st of January 1997 should be able to drive minibuses in the same way as those who sat their test before that date.  Possible solutions </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">a</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">re currently under discus</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">sion with the DfT and these should be followed through as matter of urgency, as the problem </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">reducing numbers of CT volunteers is increasing every year.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.2pt; text-indent:-32.2pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">2.5</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">To what extent should passengers in isolated communities be expected to rely on taxis and other dema</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">nd-responsive transport services? </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 49.65pt; text-indent:-49.65pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">2.5.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Improving the DRT network:</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Reliance on t</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">axis and DRT </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">as opposed to fixed route local bus services </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">could be acceptable </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">(assuming CT is </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">included in the definition of DRT) </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">providing a sufficiently diverse network exists.  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Flexible community based DRT can meet needs for many people but </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">it </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">needs investment.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">It is also imperative that the systemic discrimination that exists within the concessionary travel system that prevents many isolated people from accessing such services </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">is tackled.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.2pt; text-indent:-32.2pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">2.6</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">What are the main challenges associated with funding transport services in isolated communities? How can these services be made more affordable? </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 49.65pt; text-indent:-49.65pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">2.6.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">S</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">ervice integration </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">cross-sector benefits</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">:</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Challenges presented by the lack of integrated p</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">lanning are detailed above.  There needs to be a requirement on all publicly funded services to assess the impact of their planning and service provision in order to consider how they can integrate with other sectors.  It is also important that the real co</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">st of service provision is recognised insofar as those using or procuring services (particularly when this is done indirectly) meet the full and realistic cost of the service which they are receiving.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 49.65pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 49.65pt; text-indent:-49.65pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">2.6.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Brokerage and</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">share</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">d resources</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">:</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The default position for all publicly funded services/operators/vehicles is that they </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">should </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">be shared and accessible to the maximum number of people unless it can be shown that there is a real and pressing reason for this not to happen.  In isolated commu</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">nities, it is particularly important that scare resources are effectively utilised.  There is no reason why NHS, local authority, school or CT vehicles cannot be used to help meet the needs of groups other the</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ir</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> core clients.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 49.65pt; text-indent:-49.65pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">2.6.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Full cost recovery</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> for voluntary car schemes</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">:</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">  Hundreds (possibly thousands) of car schemes operate across the country.  Transport authorities and the NHS frequently make use of these services to support the delivery of their statutory obligations.  This engagement needs to</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> be more formally recognised and statutory agencies must pay the full cost of the services/benefits they are receiving.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 15.01pt; padding-left:20.99pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Conclusion</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.2pt; text-indent:-32.2pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">3.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The CTA has shared this evidence with its (1,500) member organisations for discussion and would be keen to expand further o</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">n those discussions and the points above through oral evidence to the Transport Committee.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_GoBack"></a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">September 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>